TY  - JOUR
AU  - Allen, Franklin
AU  - Gale, Douglas
T1  - Stock-Price Manipulation
PY  - 1992
Y1  - 1992/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/5.3.503
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 5
IS  - 3
SP  - 503
EP  - 529
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - It is generally agreed that speculators can make profits from insider trading or from the release of false information. Both forms of stock-price manipulation have now been made illegal. In this article, we ask whether it is possible to make profits from a different kind of manipulation, in which an uninformed speculator simply buys and sells shares. We show that in a rational expectations framework, where all agents maximize expected utility, it is possible for an uninformed manipulator to make a profit, provided investors attach a positive probability to the manipulator being an informed trader.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/5.3.503
ER  - 



